Anjaamai
Caption Text:
Highness, the elections are near. The people are outraged with us. Before elections,
you bow down before us to get votes. After elections, you break our backs
and demand us to bow down. You people become stooges
to the corporate companies. And sell the nation to them! Every father goes through hardship
to provide education to their children. THOSE AFFECTED BY "NEET" EXAMINATION
SHOULD NOT TAKE A PERVERSE DECISION There was a time when just pursuing
education was enough. Then, scoring grades was imperative. Now... this system decides
our student's future. Why must one endure hardship
to provide education? Why have we allowed the system to grow
and normalize this over the years? To be honest, your son is brilliant. What do you aspire
to become in the future? What is your goal in life? My goal is to become a doctor. Please don't turn my son
into a busker like you. This scheme was then approved by
the Supreme Court and implemented. If the pursued education in school
is not eligible, why should I rely on schools? TAMIL NADU PASSES BILL
AGAINST NEET EXAMS For 5000 medical seats, two lakh students
appear for the entrance exam. So, two years ago,
all the graduated doctors... followed the syllabus implemented
by the state government. You can see the students are waiting here
to write the examination. I have performed 700 open-heart surgeries. I didn't take an aptitude test. In the last ten years, only a mere 390 students from
government schools bagged medical seats. Last year,
after the aptitude test was introduced... only seven students bagged medical seats. 8 TERRITORIES ACCEPTED NEET EXAMS In India,
the other states agreed to it. What's the problem with your state? TAMIL NADU MOVES SUPREME COURT,
SAYS NEET VIOLATES BASIC STRUCTURE Sir, the people of Tamil Nadu
brim with pride and self-respect. Do you believe you'll win this case? It's not a victory
for an individual alone. It's a collective win for all of us. It's our protest. -We want justice!
-We want justice! We want... A huge war is waging upon us. If people like us set out
to break traditions, the only weapon we can wield is... education! ANJAAMAI

Title: The Secret Life of Walter Mitty
Qaidi Band
Caption Text:
A majority of prisoners in every
Indian jail are Undertrials. Undertrials are prisoners waiting
for a verdict from court. This story is about such innocent
Undertrials. Come on! Who wants to bet? If Sanju catches the rat,
you get 1.5 If the rat gets away 2.5 Do you mind if I go first? My spot is yours,
if you have 200 bucks. Scams in the toilet also? Gotta do something for expenses? You have to pay up today, my hearing is coming up
in two weeks. My lawyer says I'm getting out
for sure this time. Undertrials aren't allowed
to earn money... Should I tell the warden
you are running a business? Bloody Thief! Catch her. Independence day is coming up... this 15th August we will organize
an entertaining program. For the first time we will make
male-female orchestra party. East or West, India is the best! Where have we arrived... Baby loves to groove on bass. C'mon everybody! Rufi's poetry will be the lyrics. Maskeen will play the organ. Ogu on percussion. Sanju and Bindu will sing a duet. Russian lady and Chinese madam
will be chorus. We will have a truly
international orchestra. We're going to rock these songs... Gain points for 'good conduct'... And get acquitted at our
next hearing! I am, I am, I am, I am, I'm India! I'm yours, and you're mine... O my India! I am, I am, I am, I am, I'm India! Just look at their energy and spirit! Who would think they're
inmates of a jail. The song sung by the prisoners
of the central jail has now become... ...the new anthem of patriotism
all over the country. These prison-band songs
are going to get me votes. Don't let them get out
before the election. Done Sir. Done. Stop Maskeen Singh! You're not going to court... But sir, it's my hearing today. Ya, it's been cancelled. Sir, please don't send me
back to jail. You have no idea what life
in a jail is like! I love you. Get lost! We're innocent... but we'll rot in this jail forever. It's time for us to fly away. What has happened to us,
can happen to you too... You should take care
of your freedom.

Title: Once Upon Ay Time in Mumbaai Dobaara
Chandni
Caption Text:
My name is Chandni "I am wearing nine bangles" "Beloved, wait. I am helpless" The heart beats. Footsteps dance into
a rhythm and melody blooms "I won't listen so soon" "Take back the palanquin" "I won't go for a year or two" "Take back the palanquin" Have your ever fallen in love? No. Then fall in love once I have fallen in love...
and he's crazy and passionate "Beloved" "Amongst the many famous cities,
I'd heard the name of Delhi city" "In this Delhi city, I met a girl
called Chandni" "In her alluring eyes,
my heart drowned" You never know, at what point,
who comes into your life I don't know anything
about your life Have you ever heard the music
of the rain fall? "The dark clouds collided
with the mountains" "The water is smouldered" "The dark clouds collided
with the mountains" "The water is smouldered" "It's smouldering" Love is a gust of wind...
which takes away everything You are a different person in office... ...and a different one at home Chandni, one form is for the world... ...and the other is for oneself When your desires take the form
of words, time stands still "I will keep my desires
in your heart" "Come, my life.
I will give you my life" Have you ever heard
someone's heartbeats? "It's the monsoon season again" "My heart is suffering again!" "It's the monsoon season again" Have you ever seen the dew
falling on the flowers?  "There are sweet songs on
your lips and mine, beloved" "I walk ahead and love
follows me, beloved" Have you ever seen two sides of love? "You tell me,
I will tell you my love story!" "Who is she? How does your
dream girl look like?" When someone is in love,
there's just one tune... ...one sound and one name
on their lips "Chandni!" "O my Chandni!" "With the colourful ambience" "With the kohl of your eyes" "I have written your name
on my heart" "Chandni!" "O my Chandni!"

Title: Meri Pyaari Bindu
Caption Text:
What is love story? Boy meets girl, they
lived happily ever after. But this was my love story. I have to get some notes
from Prakash. - Where to?
- I'll be back. This 'two-phone rings' girl will
trap him. Two rings means an emergency.
You know, right? Bindu, whatever it is,
it's a no. You know, I don't like dogs. - We'll call him Devdas.
- We? Can we keep Devdas? What do I tell Maa? Instead of notes,
I came back with a dog? Come on! Bindu... In one word - she was "trouble." She always managed to make me
do wild and crazy things. Hi! I can't believe you seriously
did that. Your youth... ...my youth... We were like Gabbar and Sambha.
Munna and Circuit, Guruji and Bhola. I must tell her what I feel
about her. She already knows. Everybody knows, even people
who don't know you, know. I have seen the face
of the moon. I have seen a sky full of stars. But I have seen
no one quite like you. So I found a way to bribe life... ...and stumbled from friendship
into love. No one can stop me
from falling in love. Happy birthday! Get out of here. My heart is lost to me. Bindu's old habit. She left everything half-way. A film. A book. A hobby. God had given me so many signs. But I was too obsessed by Bindu
to ever notice. "My sweet Bindu." Many teach you how to love... ...alas no one teaches you
how to forget that love.
